column55: ih1 - 1. My ideas are usually better than other people’s ideas.
column56: ih1 - 2. For the most part, others have more to learn from me than I have to learn from them.
column57: ih1 - 3. When I am really confident in a belief, there is very little chance that belief is wrong.
column58: ih1 - 4. I’d rather rely on my own knowledge about most topics than turn to others for expertise.
column59: ih1 - 5. On important topics, I am not likely to be swayed by the viewpoints of others.
column60: ih1 - 6. I have at times changed opinions that were important to me, when someone showed me I was wrong.
column61: ih2 - 7. I am willing to change my position on an important issue in the face of good reasons.
column62: ih2 - 8. I am open to revising my important beliefs in the face of new information.
column63: ih2 - 9. I am willing to change my opinions on the basis of compelling reason.
column64: ih2 - 10. I’m willing to change my mind once it’s made up about an important topic.
column65: ih2 - 11. I respect that there are ways of making important decisions that are different from the way I make decisions.
column66: ih2 - 12. Listening to perspectives of others seldom changes my important opinions.
column67: ih3 - 13. I welcome different ways of thinking about important topics.
column68: ih3 - 14. I can have great respect for someone, even when we don't see eye-to-eye on important topics.
column69: ih3 - 15. Even when I disagree with others, I can recognize that they have sound points.
column70: ih3 - 16. When someone disagrees with ideas that are important to me, it feels as though I'm being attacked.
column71: ih3 - 17. When someone contradicts my most important beliefs, it feels like a personal attack.
column72: ih4 - 18. I tend to feel threatened when others disagree with me on topics that are close to my heart.
column73: ih4 - 19. I can respect others, even if I disagree with them in important ways.
column74: ih4 - 20. I am willing to hear others out, even if I disagree with them.
column75: ih4 - 21. When someone disagrees with ideas that are important to me, it makes me feel insignificant.
column76: ih4 - 22. I feel small when others disagree with me on topics that are close to my heart.
